http://www.chroniclelive.co.uk/news/north-east-news/ebola-military-health-workers-treated-9040886
The 3 health workers, who were flown back to the UK from Sierra Leone, were admitted to Newcastle's Royal Victoria Infirmary following direct contact with persons who were Ebola positive. After 21 days of monitoring, they were shown to have not contracted the disease]

14 Apr 2015 UK (Scotland): Ebola tests on Scot returning from west Africa comes back negative
http://news.stv.tv/scotland/317155-ebola-test-on-scot-returning-from-west-africa-comes-back-negative/
[The man had just returned to the UK from a visit to West Africa, and had just finished a course of malaria tablets. He subsequently developed possible symptoms of Ebola virus infection, and was taken to the Brownlee Center for infectious diseases at Glasgow's Gartnavel Hospital in the morning hours of Tue 14 Apr 2015. A test for Ebola virus was negative]

