Vaccines, Research
------------------
14 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: CDC launches Ebola vaccine trial in West Africa
http://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2015/p0414-ebola-vaccine.html
[On Mon 13 Apr 2015, the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (in partnership with the Sierra Leone College of Medicine and Allied Health Sciences, and the Sierra Leone Ministry of Health and Sanitation) began a clinical human (health-care workers) trial for an experimental Ebola vaccine to assess for safety and effectiveness. The trial is named "STRIVE" (Sierra Leone Trial to Introduce a Vaccine against Ebola), the name of the vaccine to be tested is rVSV-ZEBOV, and the goal enrollment goal is 6000 people]

14 Apr 2015 Sierra Leone: Healthcare workers get vaccinated for Ebola
http://www.examiner.com/article/healthcare-workers-get-vacinated-for-ebola
[Healthcare workers in the areas most heavily affected by Ebola have begun receiving a trial vaccine (VSV-ZEBOV) as part of a Phase II/III trial]

15 Apr 2015: How Ebola attacks cells?
http://ebola-virus-disease.scientificanimations.com/ebola-mechanism-of-action/
[Video of how Ebola virus commandeers other cells for replication]

